<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/332801AKTNQMQVBRHVRTTVDJGKRLVPSKP>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "2026 Compass Awards";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/c1d503ab-a15c-423d-922a-9f3183a1147b.jpeg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>The City of Kelowna presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">2026 COMPASS AWARDS</span> </h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>Join the City Manager and Senior Leadership Team in recognizing five individuals/ small teams whose actions have clearly demonstrated our values and helped build a City of the Future.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>After a fantastic 2025 filled with incredible projects, amazing collaboration, and inspiring innovations, we are thrilled to announce our 2025 winners!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Join us on Thursday, April 16th, 2026, at the Mary Irwin Theatre from 3:00 PM to 4:00 PM to celebrate the 2025 awardees:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><ul><li>Summer Effray</li><li>Marnie Douglas</li><li>Keith Pinkoski</li><li>Thomas Martin & Dennis Craig</li><li>The Adaptive Signals Project Team</li></ul><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Event Details:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Doors Open:</span> 2:45 PM<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Award Ceremony:</span> 3:00 PM - 4:00 PM<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Social Reception:</span> 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If you are attending in person, please arrive by 2:45pm. Seating will be available to our maximum capacity. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For virtual attendance, join us through the livestream!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Join us for a social hour after the ceremony.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Once the ceremony has concluded, make sure to stick around to join the winners, your colleagues and Senior Leadership for a winner's reception in the upper lobby of the Mary Irwin Theatre. Light refreshments and snacks will be provided.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Mark your calendars and come celebrate your colleagues!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets are free, pre-registration is required.
""";
