  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Ballet Kelowna presents Cikilaxʷm: Controlled Burn";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/91ad1024-a7fd-4871-9bc1-421e9fd2c5e4.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Ballet Kelowna presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Cikilaxʷm: Controlled Burn</span></h1><h2><span class=\"BoldText\">May 1 + 2, 2026</span></h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Friday at 7:30 PM / Saturday at 1:30 PM and 7:30 PM</span></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Ballet Kelowna gratefully acknowledges our 2025/26 season sponsor: <span><br/></span>The Thomas Alan Budd Foundation.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Choreography: Cameron sinkʷə Fraser-Monroe</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Composer: Cris Derksen</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Projection and Lighting Design: Andy Moro</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Costume Design: Asa Benally</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Cameron sinkʷə Fraser-Monroe returns with his newest work for the company, Cikilaxʷm: Controlled Burn, a full-length contemporary narrative ballet that blazes across time and tradition and is set to original commissioned music by Cree cellist and composer Cris Derksen. Projections by Euro/Omushkego Cree artist Andy Moro will bring to life sterile cities and scorched forests, while costumes by Navajo/Cherokee designer Asa Benally layer each character with rich histories.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Set in a dystopian future where wildfire season has no end, a young Indigenous firefighter’s beliefs are challenged when he meets Mothkʷ, a fierce protector of ancestral knowledge who carries out cultural burns.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The word cikilaxʷm [tseekiLAHkwum] means “prescribed fire” in nsyilxcən, the language belonging to the syilx (Okanagan) People. It relates to traditional burning practices that nourish the land and community, bringing healing and rejuvenation.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“This is not a tale of apocalypse, but of perseverance.<span><br/></span>Of memory that survives and endures.<span><br/></span>Of land that remembers how to heal.”<span><br/></span>- Cameron sinkʷə Fraser-Monroe<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Co-produced by the National Arts Centre’s National Creation Fund<span><br/></span>Commissioning Partner: UBCO’s Faculty of Creative and Critical Studies<span><br/></span>Other Partners Include: BC Arts Council’s Arts Impact program, Deux Mille Foundation, The Hamber Foundation, Troy Life & Fire Safety LTD., and Gord Downie & Chanie Wenjack Fund.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">Ballet Kelowna tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Thanks to the generous support of Odlum Brown, Ballet Kelowna will offer 150 accessible “Pay-What-You-Wish” seats at each performance of Cikilaxʷm: Controlled Burn. The “Pay-What-You-Wish” ticket type can be accessed by selecting a seat in section C</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Section A</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult</span> $85.50 base price + $2.10 CIF + $9.45 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$97.05</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior</span> $76.21 base price + $2.10 CIF + $9.45 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$87.76</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student/Child</span> $32.78 base price + $2.10 CIF + $7.35 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$42.23</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Section B</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult</span> $73.43 base price + $2.10 CIF + $9.45 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$84.98</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior</span> $65.12 base price + $2.10 CIF + $8.40 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$75.62</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student/Child</span> $32.78 base price + $2.10 CIF + $7.35 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$42.23</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Section C</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult</span> $62.73 base price + $2.10 CIF + $8.40 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$73.23</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior</span> $54.40 base price + $2.10 CIF + $8.40 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$64.90</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student/Child</span> $32.78 base price + $2.10 CIF + $7.35 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$42.23</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Accessible seating/Companion</span> $32.78 base price + $2.10 CIF + $7.35 service charge = <span class=\"BoldText\">$42.23</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>“Pay-What-You-Wish”<span><br/></span>$10.00 + $2.10 CIF + $1.55 service charge = $13.91<span><br/></span>$15.00 + $2.10 CIF + $1.80 service charge = $19.16<span><br/></span>$20.00 + $2.10 CIF + $2.05 service charge = $24.41<span><br/></span>$25.00 + $2.10 CIF + $2.30 service charge = $29.66<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Senior - age 65+, Student must have valid ID, Child is 12 and under.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Kelowna Community Theatre event tickets include a $2.00 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF) and 5% GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. Ballet Kelowna <span class=\"BoldText\">Restless Balance</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
