  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Black Dog - The Spirit of Led Zeppelin";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/d9ea5707-0140-440b-9b63-b64601df8de4.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>In partnership with Creative Okanagan</h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">BLACK DOG</span> </h1><h2>The Spirit of Led Zeppelin</h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>Montreal's celebrated Led Zeppelin tribute act <span class=\"ItalicText\">“Black Dog”</span> is coming to the West Coast for the first time — tickets for their 2026 shows are on sale now!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Black Dog—The Spirit of Led Zeppelin”</span> captures Led Zep's early years in a show that brings to life the essence of Led Zeppelin. From the first crushing riff of <span class=\"ItalicText\">“Whole Lotta Love”</span> to the final echos of <span class=\"ItalicText\">“Kashmir”</span> and <span class=\"ItalicText\">“Stairway to Heaven”</span>, Black Dog delivers an authentic experience with the chemistry and respect the music deserves: raw, electric, and alive.<span class=\"ItalicText\"> “If Zeppelin defines the soundtrack of your youth, this is your chance to feel it all again”</span> explains bassist Frank Larouche. <span class=\"ItalicText\">“Close your eyes, you will swear you’re back in 1973”.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With over 250 concerts to their credit and an unwavering commitment to authenticity, this powerhouse quartet channels the raw energy, soaring vocals, and legendary musicianship that made Led Zeppelin unforgettable.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://youtu.be/MdeGHY3BDyk\">Black Dog live show video: Click Here</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Special Guest: Kelowna’s own Crisprr – the rising rock band voted Kelowna’s 2025 fan favourite. Get ready for their high-voltage set before the legends take the stage.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://youtu.be/2xOUEMWjENw\">Crisprr&#39;s newest music video: Click Here</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>One night only in each city — don't miss this celebration of one of rock’s greatest legends. Claim your ticket now to be part of the experience:<span><br/></span>Apr 29 — Kamloops<span><br/></span>May 1 — Revelstoke<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">May 2 — Kelowna</span><span><br/></span>May 3 — Oliver<span><br/></span>May 5 — Chilliwack<span><br/></span>May 7 — Surrey<span><br/></span>May 8 — North Vancouver<span><br/></span>May 9 — Port Moody.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Because some music should never fade…</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular: $60.00</span> ($50.12 + $2.36 CIF + $7.52 Service Fee)<span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Black Dog - The Spirit of Led Zeppelin</span> Tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
