<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/364202ADQQQDTBPMVHTHCQQCDDCCRGDKR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "FireSmart Registration";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Protecting your community from wildfire threats begins with you!</h1><span><br/></span>Thanks for helping make our community FireSmart, Kelowna!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">The Kelowna FireSmart Community Chipping program returns this spring, with pickups scheduled to begin May 4, 2026</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This page is for registration only for the FireSmart Community Chipping Program. <span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Please Note:</span> you do not need to print any tickets for this registration - but please continue with \"buy tickets\" - once you confirm your spot you will receive an email from the Kelowna Fire Department with information around your date of pick-up. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Participants who are accepted into the program will receive an email confirming their spot, preparation requirements, and acceptable materials. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The FireSmart Community Chipping Program offers free curbside removal and chipping of select highly flammable plants and shrubs to help reduce wildfire risk on residential properties in Kelowna. Space in the program is limited, and registrations will be capped once all available pickup slots are filled. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Only select materials are considered highly flammable and eligible for pickup through this program. You will be asked to \"Is your pile only approved flammable materials?\" Please confirm that your pile consists only of cedar, juniper, mugo pine, conifer branches and prunings. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Thank you to everyone for your interest in helping reduce wildfire risk in our community! </h2>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-04T08:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
