<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/305401ASKHCQLMPSTGGQGRNQRVPMRKGGJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "High Valley";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/60512473-cda4-4881-ba9d-e2a28a71aacf.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Red Boot Live presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">HIGH VALLEY</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Canada’s powerhouse country group High Valley showcase their signature storytelling on “Along for the Ride,” the latest single from their upcoming EP Paradise & Hurricanes. The song channels the band’s trademark mix of heartfelt emotion and high-energy stompgrass sound. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“Paradise and Hurricanes seems to be the right way to summarize a relationship and a music career! Along for the Ride is really a statement song about how to take the incredible highs and lows and find the balance somewhere in the middle.  I’m Leavin You is a true statement to never ever giving up!  This whole EP says a lot if you dig into it, but on the surface, it’s some of the most fun upbeat stompgrass we’ve ever recorded!”  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With the project expected to be released in February 2026, High Valley is gearing up for a year that celebrates their highs and lows on the road - The Paradise & Hurricanes Tour. Blending real experiences with a sound that’s as familiar as it is refreshing, this season reveals the grit, grace, and heart that continue to define and shape the genre. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">ABOUT HIGH VALLEY:</span> Multi-platinum country group High Valley have cultivated a loyal following that craves the band's upbeat messages, anthemic melodies and signature fusion of contemporary country and traditional bluegrass. The musical blend has resonated with fans in the group's native Canada and the U.S. with a force that propelled High Valley to be the top-selling Canadian band in country music history.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Led by founder, lead singer/songwriter and 7-time SOCAN Country Music Award Winner Brad Rempel, the group has amassed more than half a billion global streams, notched back-to-back gold singles in the U.S., achieved multiple No. 1 songs in Canada, two gold albums and six platinum singles. High Valley has been nominated for ACM, CMT and JUNO Awards and have earned multiple CCMA Awards, with the group’s hits including \"Make You Mine,\" \"She's With Me\" and \"Grew Up On That.”\" <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 1  $63.20</span>  ($52.90 base price + $2.36 CIF + $7.94 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 2  $51.70</span>  ($42.90 base price + $2.36 CIF + $6.44 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are in CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Kelowna Community Theatre event tickets include a $2.25 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF) and 5% GST. A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">High Valley</span> tickets and their applicable service fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
