  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Laughing in the Dark Stand-up Comedy";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/903a6b1e-3754-4abb-a0ae-25c4cc451253.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Steve Taddy Comedy Ltd. presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">LAUGHING IN THE DARK STAND-UP COMEDY</span></h1><h2><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">featuring Steve Taddy & Bryan Moxon</span></span></h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Advisory: this event is for ages 19+ only.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The dark comedic stylings of <span class=\"BoldText\">Steve Taddy</span> and the twisted physicality of <span class=\"BoldText\">Bryan Moxon</span> have individually <span class=\"BoldText\">SOLD OUT over 50 stand-up comedy shows</span> across Canada. Now, <span class=\"BoldText\">on May 9th they’re joining forces</span> at the Mary Irwin Theatre in Kelowna!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Steve Taddy</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Steve Taddy was featured in the inaugural Craft Island Comedy Festival and has since performed across Western Canada with his Dark Jokes for Nice Folks comedy tour - a show centered around, you guessed it, dark humor.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>He delivers comedy for those who have a dark sense of humor but are also not terrible people (eg. no racist, or homophobic jokes here).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>These are jokes you’ll want to repeat to your co-workers and realize halfway through it’s probably not a good idea.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In 2023 Steve released his debut album, Insufferable, now streaming.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Watch clips of Steve Taddy here:</span></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0R6ejFz0blI\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0R6ejFz0blI</a><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=783wtzaoUHU\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=783wtzaoUHU</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Bryan Moxon</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A finalist in the $10k Funniest Canadian comedy competition, Bryan delivers sharp writing, dynamic act-outs, and a bit of mischief in a way that always strives to bring the audience together for a great time.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>But his proudest achievement?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“It was a great show! Apparently a lady laughed so hard at your set that she peed her pants and took her underwear off, and left them hanging in our bathroom.” — Good Times Comedy Club, Lethbridge.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Watch clips of Bryan Moxon here:</span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O8VR_oErU5w\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O8VR_oErU5w</a><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5jEx5cYieV4\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5jEx5cYieV4</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Early Bird $28.91</span>  ($22.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $4.45 service charge) <span class=\"ItalicText\">Early Bird Discount Applied at Checkout</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee. <span class=\"BoldText\">Laughing in the Dark</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
