	</table><span><br/></span>Mountains on Stage aims to bring the mountains to the city and to share all the beauty of mountain sports! A selection of the best films related to mountain activities are presented.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Information on <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.mountainsonstage.com/\">www.mountainsonstage.com</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult  $28.00</span>  ($24.35 base price + $2.36 CIF + $3.65 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student  $23.00</span>  ($17.64 base price + $2.36 CIF + $3.00 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior  $23.00</span>  ($17.64 base price + $2.36 CIF + $3.00 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Mountains on Stage</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
