<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/329401AJTLNTKPVLRLDQNRNDJNSKGRNTJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Okanagan Sun 2026 Season Ticket Packages";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/29952777-7f1f-4f8f-8aeb-89ab39892ffb.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">OKANAGAN SUN FOOTBALL CLUB</span></h1><h2><span class=\"UnderlineText\">2026 Season Ticket Packages</span> </h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>It’s under six months until Touchdown Kelowna arrives, bringing Canadian Football League regular season action to the Okanagan with two special games played by the BC Lions at the Apple Bowl. Okanagan Sun 2026 Season Ticket Packages are available starting <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"UnderlineText\">MONDAY JANUARY 19TH AT 8:00 AM</span></span> with the exclusive opportunity to secure BC Lions tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Okanagan Sun Football Club has secured 1,000 tickets per game exclusively for local football fans who support the game at the community level.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Similar “out-of-city” CFL events across Canada have sold out extremely quickly, in some cases within an hour. Purchasing an Okanagan Sun season ticket is the only guaranteed way for Okanagan football fans to access Lions tickets prior to public sale.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Important info regarding BC Lions ticket purchase opportunity:</h2>The BC Lions Football Club will play two regular season CFL games at the Apple Bowl on back-to-back Saturday afternoons:<span><br/></span><ul><li>Saturday, June 27, 2026 – BC Lions vs. Calgary Stampeders</li><li>Saturday, July 4, 2026 – BC Lions vs. Edmonton Elks</li></ul>In cooperation with the BC Lions Football Club, the BCFC’s Okanagan Sun is offering 2026 Sun season ticket purchasers an exclusive one-for-one ticket purchase opportunity for these highly anticipated games.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">One-for-One Ticket Opportunity</span><span><br/></span>Sun season ticket holders will receive a purchase code allowing them to buy BC Lions tickets on a one-for-one basis. For example:<span><br/></span><ul><li>Purchase one Sun season ticket → receive one Lions ticket purchase code</li><li>Purchase two Sun season tickets → receive two Lions ticket purchase codes</li><li>There is also the option to purchase a \"Dual Early Access\" package where one Sun season ticket → receive one Lions ticket purchase code for <span class=\"BoldText\">each</span> game date</li></ul><span class=\"BoldText\">BC Lions Advance Purchase Access</span><span><br/></span>2026 Sun season ticket holders will receive advance purchase access to these Lions games before tickets are released to the general public.<span><br/></span><ul><li>Early Bird Window: February 20 through February 24, 2026</li><li>Purchase Codes: Sent to season ticket holders prior to February 20</li><li>Ticket Purchases: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bclions.com\">Made directly through the BC Lions website HERE.</a></li></ul><h2>Okanagan Sun 2026 Season Ticket Package Options</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">1) BC Lions vs. Calgary Stampeders – June 27, 2026</span><span><br/></span>Select: <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Stampeders Early Access</span></span><span><br/></span><ul><li>Purchase one (1) Sun season ticket for $100 + $10 service charge</li><li>Provides the option to buy one (1) Lions ticket</li><li>For a pair of Lions tickets, double the purchase</li></ul><span class=\"BoldText\">2) BC Lions vs. Edmonton Elks – July 4, 2026</span><span><br/></span>Select: <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Elks Early Access</span></span><span><br/></span><ul><li>Purchase one (1) Sun season ticket for $100 + $10 service charge</li><li>Provides the option to buy one (1) Lions ticket</li><li>For a pair of Lions tickets, double the purchase</li></ul><span class=\"BoldText\">3) Both Games – June 27 & July 4, 2026</span><span><br/></span>Select: <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Dual Early Access</span></span><span><br/></span><ul><li>Purchase one (1) Sun season ticket for $150 + $15 service charge</li><li>Provides the option to buy one (1) Lions ticket for each game</li><li>For pairs of tickets, double the purchase</li></ul><span class=\"BoldText\">4) Okanagan Sun Season Ticket Purchase <span class=\"UnderlineText\">ONLY</span></span><span><br/></span>If you would like to purchase Okanagan Sun season tickets WITHOUT receiving early access to BC Lions tickets, select <span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Regular</span></span>.<span><br/></span><ul><li>Reserved Seating Sun season ticket: $90 + $9.00 service charge</li><li>General Seating Sun season ticket: $75 + $7.50 service charge</li></ul><h2>How to Purchase:</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Returning Season Ticket Holders</span>: Your seats are reserved. Please call the box office at 250-469-8940 to purchase your selected package.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">New Season Ticket Buyers</span>: Choose between Reserved Covered Stadium Seating in Sections A-D or General Admission Bleachers by clicking the seating area on the map, or using the drop-down menu above the map.<span><br/></span><ul><li>For reserved seats in Covered Stadium Seating, select your seats on the map and add them to your cart. Next, select the desired package from the \"Type\" drop-down menu. Click continue to proceed to your cart and finish checkout.</li><li>For bleacher seating in the General Admission section, type the quantity of ticket packages desired in the box next to your selected package. Click continue to proceed to your cart and finish checkout.</li></ul><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Okanagan Sun</span> season tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-01T18:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/29952777-7f1f-4f8f-8aeb-89ab39892ffb.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/location/4401APLLPBSHLDJVTLGBDQTQBHJDJSHCM>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/organization/okanagan-sun-football>;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-05-01T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

