<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/278001AVQBLRCTQCTDPTVLRHKQHJLPTRH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "RCA Presents - Barney Bentall";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/74401eb8-0685-4bfd-ad33-769d491a7200.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Rotary Centre for the Arts presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">BARNEY BENTALL</span> </h1><h2><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">My Life in Ranching and Rock & Roll</span></span></h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>Canadian music legend <span class=\"BoldText\">Barney Bentall</span>, best known as the frontman of Barney Bentall and the Legendary Hearts, brings his storied career to the stage in a powerful new solo performance. Blending songs, heartfelt stories from the ranch and road, and captivating visuals, this intimate show offers a rare glimpse into the life of one of Canada’s most celebrated singer-songwriters. Joining Barney are Cindy Fairbank on piano, accordion, and vocals, along with Kirby Barber on bass, guitar, and vocals.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Over the course of his career, Barney has earned a Juno Award for Most Promising Group of the Year, multiple Juno nominations, Canadian Country Music Association awards, and induction into both the Canadian Music Hall of Fame and the BC Entertainment Hall of Fame. These accolades reflect his contributions across decades of work in rock, country, and folk, not just his solo material, but his full journey through Canada’s musical landscape.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>From the artist: <span><br/></span>People often ask if I am going to write a book about my life. Well… this performance is my attempt to tell the story. To tell it in a way that works for me.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Through the spoken word, through my songs and with lots of visuals…. the beautiful landscapes of life on the ranch along with scenes taken from a life lived on stage, backstage, on the road and in front of a microphone. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>I hope you enjoy it.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Imagine an evening that is somewhere between Clarkson’s Farm and Springsteen on Broadway.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For more information visit: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.barneybentall.com\">https://www.barneybentall.com</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>RCA Theatre Member sales start Thursday, September 18, 2025. <span><br/></span>General public sales start Thursday, September 25, 2025. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular: $65.00</span> ($58.75 + $2.36 CIF + $6.25 Service Fee)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">30 under 30: $48.68</span> ($40.28 + $2.36 CIF + $6.04 Service Fee)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Barney Bentall</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
