<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/347601APQGGLGSJSVGLSQTVBDJPQMBPDL>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "SEEN Parent Documentary";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/ca6d2735-748b-47d7-9822-4e43d3b38a74.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Healthy Essentials Clinic presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">SEEN PARENT DOCUMENTARY</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>SEEN is an award winning feature documentary about the transformative power of personal healing for parents. Through the unfiltered and authentic narratives of real parents and science-backed insight, it shows how addressing trauma and attachment can reshape parenting and support healthy child brain development. A compelling, hopeful call to self-reflection, connection, and generational change.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>SEEN, Parent Documentary trailer here: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bZPQXpw6kT0\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bZPQXpw6kT0</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Following the documentary showing, Healthy Essentials Clinic panel of specialists will be available to answer your questions.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Also, this event will announce and introduce <span class=\"BoldText\">Parent TV</span> - a valuable resource for parents, medical practitioners, allied health professionals, student and educators. Available soon through the Okanagan Regional Library.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Assigned seating, pre-registration is encouraged, admission by donation.</span></span>
""";
