<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/353601ABQDGHHGQQMJTLKMNNMBKKDBCSS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Tempest and Triumph";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/1b01cbb0-701f-4d36-9ea3-896a70e81c5c.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Okanagan Symphony Youth Orchestra presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">TEMPEST AND TRIUMPH</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>A concert showcasing the extraordinary talents of the Okanagan Symphony Youth Orchestra (OSYO), a large ensemble of local youth musicians. Under the leadership of Conductor Zeena Zaiyouna, the OSYO undertakes one of the symphonic masterpieces of the Romantic era: Tchaikovsky’s Symphony No. 2. As a work typically performed by professional orchestras, it demands precision, endurance, and musical maturity and takes a truly unified group to bring this work to life!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The concert also features two outstanding OSYO soloists: Lenna Barbaza with Mendelssohn's Violin Concerto in E minor (1st movement) and Josh Desjarlais with Glière's Horn Concerto (1st movement).  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Witness a spectacular celebration of passion, talent, and great music!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">PROGRAM</span><span><br/></span>• Tchaikovsky — Symphony No. 2, movements 1, 2 and 4<span><br/></span> • Mendelssohn — Violin Concerto in E minor, 1st movement<span><br/></span> • Glière — Horn Concerto, 1st movement<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult  $31.46</span>  ($25.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $4.10 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior  $25.71</span>  ($20.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $3.35 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Youth - 24 and under,  free admission</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are in CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Tempest and Triumph</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
